</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E86086B2EFEF685B2FEF2F4C6" pageId="26" pageNumber="89" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586086B2EFEF685B2FEF2F4C6" blockId="26.[252,1240,2271,2909]" pageId="26" pageNumber="89">
Remarks. All four Australian forms are similar in size and ornament. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686086B2EFDF78580FB99F580" authority="Yoo" authorityName="Yoo" box="[559,1027,2548,2587]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eucochlidae" genus="Eucochlis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="89" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786086B2EFDF78580FC08F580" box="[559,914,2548,2587]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="89">Eucochlis australis</emphasis>
Yoo
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686086B2EFBF58580FE00F5D2" authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" class="Gastropoda" family="Eucochlidae" genus="Eucochlis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="89" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="depressa" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786086B2EFBF58580FE00F5D2" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="89">Eucochlis depressa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20557BC86086B2EFE668656FD8AF5D2" box="[446,528,2594,2633]" pageId="26" pageNumber="89" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686086B2EFD4B8656FCDAF5D2" authorityName="Knight" authorityYear="1933" box="[659,832,2594,2633]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eucochlidae" genus="Eucochlis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="89" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786086B2EFD4B8656FCDAF5D2" box="[659,832,2594,2633]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="89">Eucochlis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. are moderately phaneromphalous and have fine spiral threads, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686086B2EFF24860AFD0DF53E" authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[252,663,2686,2725]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eucochlidae" genus="Eucochlis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="89" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="umbiliparva" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786086B2EFF24860AFD0DF53E" box="[252,663,2686,2725]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="89">Eucochlis umbiliparva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20557BC86086B2EFD60860AFC9FF53E" box="[696,773,2686,2725]" pageId="26" pageNumber="89" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is minutely phaneromphalous and has no spiral threads. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686086B2EFC5C86DFFB4DF54F" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[900,1239,2731,2772]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eucochlidae" genus="Eucochlis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="89" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="depressa">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786086B2EFC5C86DFFB4DF54F" box="[900,1239,2731,2772]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="89">Eucochlis depressa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an exceptionally depressed final whorl, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686086B2EFF24877CFE39F4B4" authorityName="Knight" authorityYear="1933" box="[252,419,2824,2863]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eucochlidae" genus="Eucochlis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="89" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786086B2EFF24877CFE39F4B4" box="[252,419,2824,2863]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="89">Eucochlis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. has a low spire and much inflated final whorl.
</paragraph>
